\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Generating random numbers on the computer is a well known by now. Pseudo random number generators (PRNG) are fast and predictable. They require a source of information that comes from an unpredictable source to create unique sequences, this is the process we call seeding. Entropy is collected from the environment and is used to make the PRNG unpredictable. It is current wisdom that a seed cannot be constructed in software\'85 Here is how I do it.\
